						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the temple of Narēndrēśvarasvami.</p>						

						<p>14th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record can be assigned to 14th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of the temple to Narēndrēśvara linga and maintain the daily offerings for the merit of his mother Nāgamma and sister Pinnanāgamma respectively by Sarviseṭṭi. The donor Sarvisetti is described as the son of Jaluḍu Kaṁniseṭṭi.</p>						

						</summary>
